<p>1938 onwards = peoples' movement under the leadership of the All India States' People's Conference<br />
<br />
Princely states negotiating for 2 thing wd british = internal autonomy + protection of existing treaty rights&nbsp;<br />
<br />
1935 and Princely states = POLICY OF EQUAL FEDERATION</p>
<ul>
<li>federation as a constitutional demand of the princes of India.</li>
<li>demands = right to secede + protection of existing treaty rights + individual seat in legislature</li></ul>